label.value: positive regulation of tRNA C5-cytosine methylation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of tRNA C5-cytosine methylation.

label.value: formin-nucleated actin cable organization

value.value: A process that results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a formin-nucleated actin cable.

label.value: basolateral protein secretion

value.value: The controlled release of proteins from a cell at the sides which interface adjacent cells and near the base.

label.value: regulation of basement membrane organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly, disassembly or arrangement of constituent parts of the basement membrane.

label.value: protein localization to P-body

value.value: Any process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a P-body.

label.value: positive regulation of aggregation involved in sorocarp development

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of aggregation involved in sorocarp development. Aggregation involved in sorocarp development is the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the aggregate over time, from its formation to the point when a slug is formed. Aggregate development begins in response to starvation and continues by the chemoattractant-mediated movement of cells toward each other. The aggregate is a multicellular structure that gives rise to the slug.

label.value: negative regulation of aggregation involved in sorocarp development

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of aggregation involved in sorocarp development. Aggregation involved in sorocarp development is the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the aggregate over time, from its formation to the point when a slug is formed. Aggregate development begins in response to starvation and continues by the chemoattractant-mediated movement of cells toward each other. The aggregate is a multicellular structure that gives rise to the slug.

label.value: positive regulation of elastin catabolic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of elastin catabolism, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of elastin.

label.value: B-WICH complex

value.value: A chromatin remodeling complex that positively regulates histone H3 acetylation, in particular H3K9, by recruiting histone acetyltransferases to rDNA gene regions. Located in the nucleolus where it assembles on RNA Polymerase I (Pol I) and possibly on RNA Polymerase III (Pol III) promoter and coding regions during early G1 phase and activates the post-initiation phases of Pol I transcription. May also activate RNA Polymerase II (Pol II) gene transcription. In mammals, B-WICH contains the WICH complex core of BAZ1B and SMARCA5, additional protein subunits and possibly rRNAs. Although it contains several catalytic subunits it is not clear which functions are carried out by the complex itself.

definition.value: An example is BAZ1B (Q9UIG0) in human in PMID:16603771 (by IPI).

label.value: cap-independent translational initiation of linear mRNA

value.value: The process where translation initiation recruits the 40S ribosomal subunits in a cap and 5' end independent fashion before an AUG codon is encountered in an appropriate sequence context to initiate linear mRNA translation.

label.value: cap-independent translational initiation of circular RNA

value.value: The process where translation initiation recruits the 40S ribosomal subunits in a cap and 5' end independent fashion before an AUG codon is encountered in an appropriate sequence context to initiate circRNA translation.

label.value: IRES-dependent translational initiation of circular RNA

value.value: The process where translation initiation recruits the 40S ribosomal subunits via an internal ribosome entry segment (IRES) before an AUG codon is encountered in an appropriate sequence context to initiate circular mRNA translation.

label.value: regulation of actomyosin structure organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures containing both actin and myosin or paramyosin.

label.value: cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cardiac muscle myoblasts, resulting in the expansion of a cardiac muscle myoblast cell population. A cardiac myoblast is a precursor cell that has been committed to a cardiac muscle cell fate but retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life.

label.value: regulation of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation.

label.value: negative regulation of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation.

label.value: positive regulation of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation.

label.value: DNA strand resection involved in replication fork processing

value.value: The 5' to 3' exonucleolytic resection of DNA at the site of a stalled replication fork that contributes to replication fork processing.

label.value: regulation of DNA strand resection involved in replication fork processing

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of DNA strand resection involved in replication fork processing.

label.value: negative regulation of DNA strand resection involved in replication fork processing

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of DNA strand resection involved in replication fork processing.

label.value: positive regulation of mitotic spindle organization

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mitotic spindle organization.

label.value: negative regulation of meiosis I

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of meiosis I, a cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through the first phase of meiosis, in which cells divide and homologous chromosomes are paired and segregated from each other, producing two daughter cells.

label.value: regulation of G2/MI transition of meiotic cell cycle

value.value: Any signaling pathway that modulates the activity of a cell cycle cyclin-dependent protein kinase to modulate the switch from G2 phase to MI phase of the meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: negative regulation of G2/MI transition of meiotic cell cycle

value.value: Any signaling pathway that decreases or inhibits the activity of a cell cycle cyclin-dependent protein kinase to modulate the switch from G2 phase to MI phase of the meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: positive regulation of G2/MI transition of meiotic cell cycle

value.value: Any signaling pathway that activates or increases the activity of a cell cycle cyclin-dependent protein kinase to modulate the switch from G2 phase to MI phase of the meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: regulation of adenylate cyclase-activating glucose-activated G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the adenylate cyclase-activating glucose-activated G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway, the series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of glucose binding to a G protein-coupled receptor, where the pathway proceeds with activation of adenylyl cyclase and a subsequent increase in the concentration of cyclic AMP (cAMP).

label.value: negative regulation of adenylate cyclase-activating glucose-activated G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the adenylate cyclase-activating glucose-activated G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway.

label.value: rDNA spacer replication fork barrier binding, bending

value.value: The activity of binding selectively, and in a sequence-specific manner, a replication fork barrier found in rDNA spacers, and distorting the original structure of DNA, typically a straight helix, into a bend, or increasing the bend if the original structure was intrinsically bent due to its sequence.

label.value: C2 domain binding

value.value: Binding to the C2 domain of a protein, a protein structural domain involved in targeting proteins to cell membranes.

label.value: regulation of nematode male tail tip morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of nematode male tail tip morphogenesis, the process in which the anatomical structure of the adult male tail tip is generated and organized.

label.value: negative regulation of nematode male tail tip morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of nematode male tail tip morphogenesis.

label.value: positive regulation of nematode male tail tip morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of nematode male tail tip morphogenesis.

label.value: nematode pharynx morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the anatomical structures of the nematode pharynx are generated and organized.

label.value: regulation of nematode pharynx morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of nematode pharynx morphogenesis, the process in which the anatomical structure of the pharynx is generated and organized.

label.value: negative regulation of nematode pharynx morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of nematode pharynx morphogenesis.

label.value: positive regulation of nematode pharynx morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of nematode pharynx morphogenesis.

label.value: regulation of cell cycle switching, mitotic to meiotic cell cycle

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of mitotic to meiotic cell cycle switching, the process in which a cell switches cell cycle mode from mitotic to meiotic division.

label.value: negative regulation of cell cycle switching, mitotic to meiotic cell cycle

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of mitotic to meiotic cell cycle switching, the process in which a cell switches cell cycle mode from mitotic to meiotic division.

label.value: deaminated glutathione amidase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: N-(4-oxoglutarate)-L-cysteinylglycine + H2O = 2-oxoglutarate + L-cysteinylglycine.

label.value: metabolite repair

value.value: A cellular process that, through single- or multi-step enzymatic reactions, repairs useless or toxic endogenous compounds, formed as by-products of primary metabolism, by converting them into useful metabolites.

label.value: toxic metabolite repair

value.value: A cellular process that, through single- or multi-step enzymatic reactions, repairs toxic endogenous compounds, formed as by-products of primary metabolism, by converting them into useful metabolites.

label.value: regulation of actin filament organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of actin filament organization.

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of actin filament annealing, i.e. the end-to-end joining of existing actin filaments.

label.value: negative regulation of actin filament annealing

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of actin filament annealing, i.e. the end-to-end joining of existing actin filaments.

label.value: positive regulation of actin filament annealing

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of actin filament annealing, i.e. the end-to-end joining of existing actin filaments.

label.value: regulation of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation.

label.value: positive regulation of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation.

label.value: negative regulation of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation.

label.value: regulation of angiotensin-activated signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the angiotensin-activated signaling pathway.

label.value: negative regulation of angiotensin-activated signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the angiotensin-activated signaling pathway.
